subname: DESIGN OF PRE STRESSED CONCRETE ELEMENTS
m1desc:
Introduction and Analysis of Members:
Concept of Prestressing - Types of Prestressing - Advantages - Limitations –Prestressing systems - Anchoring devices - Materials - Mechanical Properties of high strength concrete - high strength steel - Stress-Strain curve for High strength concrete.Analysis of members at transfer - Stress concept - Comparison of behavior of reinforced concrete - prestressed concrete - Force concept - Load balancing concept - Kern point Pressure line.
m2desc:
Losses in Prestress:
Loss of Prestress due to Elastic shortening, Friction, Anchorage slip, Creep of concrete, Shrinkage of concrete and Relaxation of steel - Total Loss. Deflection and Crack Width Calculations of Deflection due to gravity loads - Deflection due to prestressing force -Total deflection - Limits of deflection - Limits of span-toeffective depth ratio -Calculation of Crack Width - Limits of crack width.
m3desc:
Design of Sections for Flexure:
Analysis of members at ultimate strength - Preliminary Design - Final Design for Type 1members.
m4desc:
Design for Shear:
Analysis for shear - Components of shear resistance - Modes of Failure - Limit State of collapse for shear - Design of transverse reinforcement.
m5desc:
Composite Sections:
Types of composite construction - Analysis of composite sections - Deflection –Flexural and shear strength of composite sections.
